rs thus advance an existential critique of abstract globalization discourse. The book enriches interdisciplinary debates about hitherto neglected aspects of contemporary cosmopolitanism as a political and moral project, examining the form of its lived effects and offering new ideas and case studies to work with.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCosmopolitanismvCase studies. 0aCulture and globalizationvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aEriksen, Thomas Hylland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrønseth, Anne Sigfrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Alexandra, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJosephides, Lisette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJosephides, Lisette, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRapport, Nigel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchiltz, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStade, Ronald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311099823840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178238277540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782382775423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782382775/original  a978-3-11-099823-8  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK